data.enText: -ies
protection
the activities involved in protecting a country, building or person against attack, danger, etc.
national security (= the defence of a country)
airport security

data.chText: 他们在机场实行了安全检查。
data.enText: They carried out security checks at the airport.

data.chText: 访问是在戒备森严的情况下进行的。
data.enText: The visit took place amidst tight security (= the use of many police officers) .
the security forces/services (= the police, army, etc.)

data.chText: 高度 / 最高级戒备的监狱
data.enText: a high/maximum security prison (= for dangerous criminals)

data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的不可数名词

data.enText: the department of a large company or organization that deals with the protection of its buildings, equipment and staff

data.chText: 保安人员被叫到事发现场。
data.enText: Security was/were called to the incident.
protection against sth bad that might happen in the future
financial security

data.chText: 稳定的工作是过去的事了。
data.enText: Job security (= the guarantee that you will keep your job) is a thing of the past.
feeling happy/safe
the state of feeling happy and safe from danger or worry
the security of a loving family life

data.chText: 她不自觉地陷入了一种虚假的安全感之中。
data.enText: She'd allowed herself to be lulled into a false sense of security (= a feeling that she was safe when in fact she was in danger) .
for a loan
a valuable item, such as a house, that you agree to give to sb if you are unable to pay back the money that you have borrowed from them

data.chText: 他是以房子和店铺为抵押得到这笔贷款的。
data.enText: His home and business are being held as security for the loan.
shares in company
documents proving that sb is the owner of shares, etc. in a particular company

simple_means.memory_skill: se 分开，离开 + cur 跑，引申为“发生” + ity 具备某种性质 → 安全；证券

tr: measures taken as a precaution against theft or espionage or sabotage etc.
example: military security has been stepped up since the recent uprising

tr: an electrical device that sets off an alarm when someone tries to break in
a guarantee that an obligation will be met

example: the watch dog gave her a feeling of security

tr: a department responsible for the security of the institution's property and workers
example: the head of security was a former policeman
his pension gave him security in his old age
insurance provided protection against loss of wages due to illness

tr: property that your creditor can claim in case you default on your obligation
example: bankers are reluctant to lend without good security

tr: a formal declaration that documents a fact of relevance to finance and investment
the holder has a right to receive interest or dividends
the state of being free from danger or injury
example: we support the armed services in the name of national security

value.def: Security refers to all the measures that are taken to protect a place, or to ensure that only people with permission enter it or leave it.

example.ex: They are now under a great deal of pressure to tighten their airport security...
example.tran: 他们现在承受着加强机场安保措施的巨大压力。

example.ex: Strict security measures are in force in the capital.
example.tran: 首都采取了严密的安全措施。
一所实行最高警戒的监狱

value.tran: 防卫;保安措施;安全工作

value.def: A feeling of security is a feeling of being safe and free from worry.

example.ex: He loves the security of a happy home life...
example.tran: 他喜欢幸福家庭生活所带来的安全感。

example.ex: If an alarm gives you that feeling of security, then it's worth carrying.
example.tran: 如果带着闹钟让你感到心里踏实，那就值得携带。

defx.def: If something gives you a false sense of security, it makes you believe that you are safe when you are not.

example.ex: Wearing helmets gave cyclists a false sense of security and encouraged them to take risks.
example.tran: 戴头盔给骑自行车的人一种错误的安全感，怂恿他们去冒险。

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft N <l>of</l> n

value.def: If something is security for a loan, you promise to give that thing to the person who lends you money, if you fail to pay the money back.

example.ex: The central bank will provide special loans, and the banks will pledge the land as security.
example.tran: 中央银行会提供特殊贷款，而这些银行会以土地作为抵押。

value.def: Securities are stocks, shares, bonds, or other certificates that you buy in order to earn regular interest from them or to sell them later for a profit.

example.ex: National banks can package their own mortgages and underwrite them as securities.
example.tran: 国家银行能够合并自己的抵押贷款并以证券形式包销。
